  "texts": [
    "The normality can be tested here with the Shapiro-Wilk test 54 (shapiro in the package scipy.stats and shapiro.test in the package stats in R).",
    "If the data is not normally distributed, the possible alternatives for the F-test include Barlett's test 55 (bartlett in scipy.stats in Python and bartlett.test in stats in R) and Levene's test 56 (levene in scipy.stats in Python and leveneTest in the package car 57 in R).",
    "In ML research, it is often of interest if a specific ML model performs better than a human.",
    "Especially, in a medical field, it is useful to estimate the difference between the tumor masks predicted by a CNN differ and those drawn by a physician by taking into account how much difference there would be if the same masks were drawn by two different physicians.",
    "For this purpose, we can use statistical testing to compare the results of an ML model and a human in terms of a relevant evaluation metric as we would compare the performance of two models."
